# Mobile Responsive Design

All UI must be **mobile-first** and fully responsive. Design for the smallest screen first, then enhance for larger breakpoints.

## Tailwind Breakpoint Strategy

Use Tailwind's mobile-first breakpoints — base styles target mobile, then layer up:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — mobile-first
<div className="px-4 py-6 sm:px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-12">
  <h1 className="text-xl sm:text-2xl lg:text-3xl">Title</h1>
</div>

// ❌ WRONG — desktop-first, overriding down
<div className="px-12 md:px-8 sm:px-6">
```

## Layout Rules

- Use `flex-col` on mobile, switch to `flex-row` at `sm:` or `md:` breakpoints
- Set `max-w-screen-xl mx-auto` on main content containers with horizontal padding (`px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`)
- Use CSS Grid with responsive columns: `grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4`
- Avoid fixed widths — use `w-full`, `max-w-`, and percentage-based sizing
- Sidebars should collapse to a hamburger menu or bottom sheet on mobile (`hidden md:block`)

## Typography

- Base font size should be readable on mobile (minimum `text-sm` / 14px for body)
- Scale headings with breakpoints: `text-lg sm:text-xl lg:text-2xl`
- Line lengths: cap at `max-w-prose` for readability on wide screens

## Touch Targets

- All interactive elements must have a minimum touch target of 44x44px on mobile
- Use `min-h-[44px] min-w-[44px]` or adequate padding (`p-3` minimum) on buttons and links
- Ensure adequate spacing between tap targets (`gap-3` minimum in button groups)

## Images & Media

- Always use responsive images: `w-full h-auto` or `object-cover` with aspect-ratio containers
- Use `aspect-video` or `aspect-square` for consistent media sizing
- Lazy load off-screen images with `loading="lazy"`

## Forms

- Inputs should be `w-full` on mobile
- Stack form fields vertically on mobile, allow side-by-side at `sm:` or wider
- Use `text-base` (16px) on inputs to prevent iOS zoom on focus

## Testing Mindset

- Always visually verify layouts at 320px, 375px, 768px, 1024px, and 1440px widths
- Ensure no horizontal scroll at any breakpoint
- Navigation must be fully accessible on mobile (hamburger menu, swipe-friendly)
